<h3><a href="http://alexschroeder.ch/wiki/Diary" title="Alex Schroeder: Diary">Alex Schroeder</a></h3>


<div class="entrygroup" id="http://alexschroeder.ch/wiki/2014-02-12_Red_Cliff">
<h4><a href="http://alexschroeder.ch/wiki/2014-02-12_Red_Cliff">Red Cliff</a></h4>
<div class="entry">
<div class="content">
<p>I enjoyed <a class="movie" href="http://www.google.com/search?ie=UTF-8&oe=UTF-8&q=Red+Cliff+2008"><cite>Red Cliff</cite> (<cite>2008</cite>)</a> even though it contained far more battle than I cared for. I liked Tony Leung. I kept thinking about the <em>Three Kingdoms</em> Book I started to read and the episodes of the <a class="url http outside" href="http://chinahistorypodcast.com/">Chinese History Podcast</a> on the end of the Han, the Three Kingdoms Period, Daoism, the huge ships and formidable weapons the Chinese had.</p><p><img class="smiley" src="http://www.emacswiki.org/pics/star.png" alt="star" /> <img class="smiley" src="http://www.emacswiki.org/pics/star.png" alt="star" /> <img class="smiley" src="http://www.emacswiki.org/pics/star.png" alt="star" /> – I&#x2019;d recommend it to anybody who likes the genre</p><p>Tags: <a class="outside tag" title="Tag" rel="tag" href="http://alexschroeder.ch/wiki?action=tag;id=Movies">Movies</a> <a class="feed tag" title="Feed for this tag" rel="feed" href="http://alexschroeder.ch/wiki/feed/full/Movies"><img src="http://alexschroeder.ch/pics/rss.png" alt="RSS" /></a></p></div>







