<h4><a href="http://alexschroeder.ch/wiki/2014-01-23_Fight_On">Fight On</a></h4>
<div class="entry">
<div class="content">
<p><a class="near" title="Names" href="http://www.fightonmagazine.com/">Fight On</a>! #14 has been <a class="url http outside" href="http://www.lulu.com/spotlight/FightOn">released on Lulu</a>! The bestest old school fanzine is back, like a revenant it haunts the living even if we know that <em>it is already dead.</em> Calithena has said that <a class="local" href="http://alexschroeder.ch/wiki/2013-02-12_Fight_On_is_going_down">#15 will be the last issue</a> and that saddens me. Issue #14 also came without my <a class="local" href="http://alexschroeder.ch/wiki/Caverns_of_Slime">Caverns of Slime</a>. This doesn&#x2019;t make me as sad as I thought it would because we get a fantastic troll fortress instead. Gatehouse, temple, main complex, it has everything and nice, emphatic maps. Thick, black lines, high contrast edges, and yet clearly labelled. <em>Citadel of the Dark Trolls.</em> <a class="url http outside" href="http://xolgmod.blogspot.com/">Lee Barber</a>. Well done!</p><p>One of the comments in <a class="url http outside" href="http://odd74.proboards.com/thread/9645/fight-on-released-print-pdf">the announcement thread</a> says &#x201c;I used the code GETIT25 and got 25% off my order.&#x201d; Good luck!</p><p>Tags: <a class="outside tag" title="Tag" rel="tag" href="http://alexschroeder.ch/wiki?action=tag;id=RPG">RPG</a> <a class="feed tag" title="Feed for this tag" rel="feed" href="http://alexschroeder.ch/wiki/feed/full/RPG"><img src="http://alexschroeder.ch/pics/rss.png" alt="RSS" /></a> <a class="outside tag" title="Tag" rel="tag" href="http://alexschroeder.ch/wiki?action=tag;id=Old%20School">Old School</a> <a class="feed tag" title="Feed for this tag" rel="feed" href="http://alexschroeder.ch/wiki/feed/full/Old%20School"><img src="http://alexschroeder.ch/pics/rss.png" alt="RSS" /></a></p></div>







