<h3><a href="http://alexschroeder.ch/wiki/Diary" title="Alex Schroeder: Diary">Alex Schroeder</a></h3>


<div class="entrygroup" id="http://alexschroeder.ch/wiki/2014-01-17_Monitoring">
<h4><a href="http://alexschroeder.ch/wiki/2014-01-17_Monitoring">Monitoring</a></h4>
<div class="entry">
<div class="content">
<p>I followed the tutorial <a class="url http outside" href="http://www.howtoforge.com/server-monitoring-with-munin-and-monit-on-debian-wheezy-p2">Server Monitoring With munin And monit On Debian Wheezy</a> by Falko Timme and I think it worked! I made some small additions in order to monitor Exim4 and Dovecot based on the <a class="url http outside" href="http://mmonit.com/wiki/Monit/ConfigurationExamples">Monit configuration examples</a> on their wiki and some notes on <a class="url http outside" href="https://wiki.debian.org/Self-Signed_Certificate">self-signed certificates</a> from the Debian wiki.</p><p>For my future self trying to figure out what the hell is going on:</p><ul><li><a class="url http" href="http://alexschroeder.ch/munin/">http://alexschroeder.ch/munin/</a> has the nice pictures (Munin)</li><li><a class="url http" href="https://alexschroeder.ch:2812/">https://alexschroeder.ch:2812/</a> has the alerting and restarting capabilities (Monit)</li></ul><p>Nice! <img class="smiley" src="http://www.emacswiki.org/pics/ok.png" alt="ok" /></p><p>Tags: <a class="outside tag" title="Tag" rel="tag" href="http://alexschroeder.ch/wiki?action=tag;id=Admin">Admin</a> <a class="feed tag" title="Feed for this tag" rel="feed" href="http://alexschroeder.ch/wiki/feed/full/Admin"><img src="http://alexschroeder.ch/pics/rss.png" alt="RSS" /></a></p></div>







