<div class="channelgroup">







<h3><a href="http://scripting.com/" title="Scripting News">Dave Winer</a></h3>


<div class="entrygroup" id="http://scripting.com/2014/01/01/whatWouldAPublicNotepadDo.html" lang="en-us">
<h4><a href="http://scripting.com/2014/01/01/whatWouldAPublicNotepadDo.html">What would a &amp;quot;public notepad&amp;quot; do?</a></h4>
<div class="entry">
<div class="content">
<p>First question of the new year. </p>
				<p>Yesterday I <a href="http://scripting.com/2013/12/31/twitterAsANotepad">wrote</a> about using Twitter as a "public notepad."</p>
				<p>Sure, the note-putting part of it was great. One item after another in rapid-fire, with the ability of people to add or comment. Most of it was pretty civil because.. Well I don't know why. </p>
				<p>But when it came time to gather it all up and present it as a matter of record, that was a lot of hard work, and the result wasn't very satisfying. </p>
				<p>So how would it work?</p></div>







