<h3><a href="http://alexschroeder.ch/wiki/Diary" title="Alex Schroeder: Diary">Alex Schroeder</a></h3>


<div class="entrygroup" id="http://alexschroeder.ch/wiki/2013-12-31_Scanner_Again">
<h4><a href="http://alexschroeder.ch/wiki/2013-12-31_Scanner_Again">Scanner Again</a></h4>
<div class="entry">
<div class="content">
<p>We decided to switch from the Apple Mac Mini running Mac OS 10.6.8 (since it&#x2019;s such an old machine it cannot be upgraded) to Claudia&#x2019;s 13&#x201d; Powerbook running the latest Mac OS 10.9.1.</p><p>And, as always, the old CanoScan LiDE 25 doesn&#x2019;t work. The latest drivers are for Mac OS 10.6 &#x2013; yay. I found <a class="url http outside" href="http://macmanus.nl/2013/11/28/use-unsupported-scanner-in-mavericks/">fixed : use unsupported scanner in OSX 10.9 Mavericks</a>] which had me install some promising libs. But it didn&#x2019;t work. The Printer &amp; Scanner preference pane never found the old scanner, and on the command line I didn&#x2019;t get the scanner listed.</p><p>I decided to give <a class="local" href="http://alexschroeder.ch/wiki/Homebrew">Homebrew</a> a try and installed <strong>sane-backends</strong>. This required a painful and slow uninstalling of libusb and the sane-backends installed by the promising libs I had just installed.</p><p>Using the sane-backends installed by Homebrew, I can now scan from the command line. Oh well, better than nothing.</p><pre class="real">alex@Megabombus:~$ scanimage -L
device `plustek:libusb:004:002' is a Canon CanoScan LiDE25 flatbed scanner
Trace/BPT trap: 5
alex@Megabombus:~$ scanimage --device=plustek:libusb:004:002 --format=tiff --mode=color --resolution=300 -l 0 -t 0 -x 215 -y 297 &gt; Desktop/scan.tiff
Killed: 9
alex@Megabombus:~$ open Desktop/scan.tiff </pre><p>It works. <img class="smiley" src="http://www.emacswiki.org/pics/ok.png" alt="ok" /></p><p>Since the scanner is not supported by Image Capture, I can&#x2019;t use it to scan from Gimp. <img class="smiley" src="http://www.emacswiki.org/pics/sucks.png" alt="sucks" /></p><p>The TWAIN-SANE-Interface and the SANE-Preference-Pane I installed appear to be useless. Oh well. <img class="smiley" src="http://www.emacswiki.org/pics/sucks.png" alt="sucks" /></p><div>&#x262f;</div><p>And now that I have scanned the picture I just need to reinstall <a class="url http outside" href="http://www.tug.org/mactex/">Tex Live 2013</a> since the migration appears to have failed. <img class="smiley" src="http://www.emacswiki.org/pics/sucks.png" alt="sucks" /></p><p>Tags: <a class="outside tag" title="Tag" rel="tag" href="http://alexschroeder.ch/wiki?action=tag;id=OSX">OSX</a> <a class="feed tag" title="Feed for this tag" rel="feed" href="http://alexschroeder.ch/wiki/feed/full/OSX"><img src="http://alexschroeder.ch/pics/rss.png" alt="RSS" /></a> <a class="outside tag" title="Tag" rel="tag" href="http://alexschroeder.ch/wiki?action=tag;id=Scanner">Scanner</a> <a class="feed tag" title="Feed for this tag" rel="feed" href="http://alexschroeder.ch/wiki/feed/full/Scanner"><img src="http://alexschroeder.ch/pics/rss.png" alt="RSS" /></a></p></div>







<p class="date">
<a href="http://alexschroeder.ch/wiki/2013-12-31_Scanner_Again">December 31, 2013 01:44 PM</a>
</p>
</div>
